od that is declared without a body is known as?','Static method','Final method','Abstract method','Private method','C'),(387,'Abstraction','Which keyword is used by a class to use an interface?','extends','inherits','implements','uses','C'),(388,'Abstraction','Can an abstract class have a main method?','Yes','No','Only if it is public','Only if it is not abstract','A'),(389,'Abstraction','Which of these cannot be declared abstract?','Class','Method','Variable','All of the above','C'),(390,'Abstraction','The process of focusing on essential features is called?','Encapsulation','Polymorphism','Abstraction','Inheritance','C'),(391,'Abstraction','If a class contains at least one abstract method, it must be?','Static','Final','Abstract','Private','C'),(392,'Abstraction','Can an abstract class have a constructor?','Yes','No','Only if it is final','Only if it is static','A'),(393,'Abstraction','Can an abstract class be declared as final?','Yes','No','Only if it has no methods','Only if it is public','B'),(394,'Abstraction','An abstract class can contain ______?','Abstract methods only','Non-abstract methods only','Both abstract and non-abstract methods','None of the above','C'),(395,'Abstraction','What happens if a child class does not implement all abstract methods of its parent?','It compiles fine','It must also be declared abstract','Runtime error','It becomes an interface','B'),(396,'Abstraction','Can an abstract class extend another concrete class?','Yes','No','Only if the parent is final','Only in the same package','A'),(397,'Abstraction','Which modifier cannot be used with an abstract method?','public','protected','private','None of the above','C'),(398,'Abstraction','Is it mandatory for an abstract class to have an abstract method?','Yes','No','Only if it is public','Only if it is final','B'),(399,'Abstraction','Can abstract methods be static?','Yes','No','Only if the class is static','Only in interfaces','B'),(400,'Abstraction','The \"abstract\" keyword can be applied to?','Methods only','Classes only','Both methods and classes','Variables','C'),(401,'Abstraction','By default, all methods in an interface are ______?','public and abstract','private and static','protected and abstract','public and final','A'),(402,'Abstraction','How many interfaces can a single class implement?','Only one','Only two','Multiple','Zero','C'),(403,'Abstraction','Variables in an interface are implicitly ______?','public, static, and final','private and final','protected and static','public and volatile','A'),(404,'Abstraction','Which keyword is used for an interface to extend another interface?','implements','extends','inherits','includes','B'),(405,'Abstraction','Since Java 8, interfaces can have ______?','Static methods','Default methods','Both A and B','Private methods','C'),(406,'Abstraction','Can we instantiate an interface?','Yes','No','Only with the new keyword','Only if it is empty','B'),(407,'Abstraction','An interface with no methods is called a ______?','Functional Interface','Marker Interface','Abstract Interface','Empty Interface','B'),(408,'Abstraction','The purpose of an interface is to achieve ______?','Loose coupling','Multiple inheritance','Both A and B','Tight coupling','C'),(409,'Abstraction','Can an interface have a constructor?','Yes','No','Only if it is static','Only if it is empty','B'),(410,'Abstraction','What is the access modifier for interface variables by default?','private','protected','public','default','C'),(411,'Abstraction','What is a functional interface?','An interface with many methods','An interface with exactly one abstract method','An interface with no methods','A class with one method','B'),(412,'Abstraction','Which annotation is used to ensure an interface is functional?','@Functional','@Interface','@FunctionalInterface','@Abstract','C'),(413,'Abstraction','Can an interface have private methods?','No','Yes, since Java 9','Yes, since Java 8','Only if they are static','B'),(414,'Abstraction','Default methods