ement the methods of an interface it implements?','Mandatory','Optional','Only if final','Only if static','B'),(428,'Abstraction','Which of these is a similarity between abstract class and interface?','Both can have constructors','Both cannot be instantiated','Both can have private methods','Both can have non-final variables','B'),(429,'Abstraction','Which is a \"Contract\" in programming?','Class','Object','Interface','Variable','C'),(430,'Abstraction','Which design principle does Abstraction support?','DRY (Don\'t Repeat Yourself)','DIP (Dependency Inversion Principle)','KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid)','None','B'),(431,'Abstraction','Is \"abstract public void test();\" a valid declaration?','Yes','No','Only in interfaces','Only in concrete classes','A'),(432,'Abstraction','Can we use the \"native\" keyword with \"abstract\"?','Yes','No','Only for static methods','Only in interfaces','B'),(433,'Abstraction','Which of these is used to hide internal details?','Abstraction','Encapsulation','Both A and B','Neither','C'),(434,'Abstraction','Can we use \"synchronized\" with \"abstract\"?','Yes','No','Only in abstract classes','Only for static methods','B'),(435,'Abstraction','What happens if you try to call an abstract method?','Compilation error','Runtime error','It returns null','It returns 0','A'),(436,'Abstraction','Can a class be abstract without any abstract methods?','Yes','No','Only if it is final','Only in Java 8+','A'),(437,'Abstraction','Abstract classes are useful for ______?','Templates','Fixed implementations','Final data','Speed','A'),(438,'Abstraction','Can an interface be local (inside a method)?','Yes','No','Only since Java 17','Only if static','B'),(439,'Abstraction','Can an abstract class be nested?','Yes','No','Only if it is static','Only if private','A'),(440,'Abstraction','Which of these is an example of abstraction in real life?','A car engine','A remote control','A computer mouse','All of the above','D'),(441,'Abstraction','Can static methods be d