e;','protected int score;','static int score;','B'),(527,'Encapsulation','Encapsulation makes code ______?','Harder to maintain','Easier to maintain/modify','Slower to execute','Dependent on other classes','B'),(528,'Encapsulation','Can encapsulation be bypassed using Java Reflection?','No','Yes','Only for public methods','Only in Java 8','B'),(529,'Encapsulation','A POJO class is usually ______?','Inherited','Abstract','Encapsulated','Static','C'),(530,'Encapsulation','Is encapsulation a compile-time or runtime concept?','Compile-time','Runtime','Both','None','C'),(531,'Encapsulation','Can a constructor be private?','Yes','No','Only if static','Only if abstract','A'),(532,'Encapsulation','A private constructor is often used in which pattern?','Factory','Singleton','Strategy','Observer','B'),(533,'Encapsulation','What is the relation between Encapsulation and \"Loose Coupling\"?','Encapsulation increases coupling','Encapsulation helps achieve loose coupling','They are unrelated','They are opposites','B'),(534,'Encapsulation','Which keyword helps the setter distinguish between a parameter and a class field?','super','this','parent','base','B'),(535,'Encapsulation','Can we encapsulate an interface?','Yes','No','Only if it has default methods','Only if static','B'),(536,'Encapsulation','Encapsulation focuses on the ______ of data.','Validation','Storage','Security and Control','Speed','C'),(537,'Encapsulation','Which modifier is used to protect members from outside packages but not subclasses?','public','private','protected','default','C'),(538,'Encapsulation','Is \"Information Hiding\" exactly the same as \"Encapsulation\"?','Yes','Technically Hiding is a result of Encapsulation','No, they are opposites','None','B'),(539,'Encapsulation','Can an abstract class be encapsulated?','Yes','No','Only if final','Only if static','A'),(540,'Encapsulation','What is the primary benefit of encapsulation in team projects?','Less code','Code can be changed without breaking others\' 